1-# Keycloak-client libraries
2-
3:Keycloak-client is a set of Java libraries, which can be used in the client applications to invoke Keycloak server public 
4-APIs. This include Keycloak admin REST API and API for calling authorization services or enforcing access decisions by using 
5-policy enforcer.
--
9-* [authorization-client](authz-client) - Java library for invoke Authorization API
10-* [policy-enforcer](policy-enforcer) - Java library for enforce authorization decisions. It consumes the authorization-client
11:* [common module](client-common-synced) - Common classes and JSON representation mapping classes, which are used by other 
12-  libraries from above 
13:* [documentation](docs) - Documentation
14:* [testsuite](testsuite) - Testsuite
15-
16-The client libraries have release lifecycle independent of Keycloak server releases. The libraries don't have any direct 
17-dependency on Keycloak server libraries.  
